22:00:00","eventDescription":"Dignitary is a Los Angeles based darkly romantic post-punk band.

Band leader and vocalist Mike Cuenca, guitarist Gabe Huerta, and bassist Fallon Scherzinger are the official members of the group with guest performers filling in for live shows. Formerly Dignitary Loss, in 2015 Cuenca reintroduced the band as Dignitary with the debut five-song Tautology EP.

Drawing comparison to bands like Echo & the Bunnymen, Pulp, and The Cure, Dignitary employs high energy reverb alongside crooning vocal harmonies to create two-to-three minute long hook-filled pop songs. Songs about heartbreak, failure, and the unknown; a healthy obsession with all things supernatural and occult, yet with a dark sense of humor.

Dignitary is now set to release their two years in the making debut LP Full Moon in Vertigo via Burger Records subsidiary Wiener Records. The fifteen-track album, which was self-produced and recorded in lead singer/songwriter's Mike Cuenca's home, will be the first of three albums to be released by the prolific band within the next year. 

"Conjuring a kind of ghostly, Gun Clubbed menace, full of modern portent and yearning smarts, the sound Dignitary make isn't a long way from what Lee Hazlewood might have sounded like if he'd come of age in 1980." - Stereo Embers Magazine

"The LA outfit has clearly been influenced by the voluminous excellence of 80s synth and new romantic bands, while adding their own sulky spin on California dreaming." - Fuzzy Logic

"They perfectly capture the feel of "sunny day rain" that The Jesus and Mary Chain sang about. As if Robert Smith visited a beach and stared at the sea in broad daylight." - The Revue

"Their initial single, "Demon, Beside Me" is a thematically and sonically apt introduction, echoing Gothic folk that hints at the dark sides explored by the likes of Nick Cave and X.
